## When to use
When you need to analyze and troubleshoot issues related to disk performance in a Linux system.
## Approach
Use the `shell_exec` tool with the `iostat` command. Consider using advanced options like `-d` for displaying only device-specific statistics, or `-x` for extended statistics including CPU statistics as well. Use `ssh_exec_background` if you need continuous monitoring.
## Example
```sh
shell_exec "iostat -dx 5"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run `iostat` with device-specific and extended statistics, displaying output every 5 seconds for detailed disk I/O analysis over time.
## Pitfalls
- Ensure that the system has the necessary permissions to execute `iostat`.
- Be aware of how frequently you run `iostat` as it can add some overhead to your system.